I don’t feel like it’s a goodbye to Montreal because we will be back so often but I do feel like it’s a goodbye to our home and our neighborhood. There’s a lot of feelings and emotions which I will go in to later, already cried on the plane and we haven’t even taken off yet 🙈so I need to keep it pulled together for now. But our hearts will always be in Montreal 🤍
I don’t know if you could call losing every game a successful tournament but we had so much fun!

Oh man, and I thought millie did me dirty the night she learned to crawl out of her crib! I couldn’t seem to get Linc to go to sleep the last two nights so tonight after a two hour crying match (tears were had by all) he hurled himself out of the crib. A night I desperately needed to get the kids to bed so I could finish packing up for our camping trip, something I was already stressed about all day. 
Now that the tears are gone and I’m looking at this sweet little baby sleeping next to me, I can’t help but think about everything that has gone in the last 9 days. Such big changes, a lot of emotions, and a lot of stress. Of course he is going to have a bit of a hard time, and I need to find the patience and give him a little more grace. Not only for him but for the girls and even myself. I have hated myself this week. I have been so short tempered with the girls, I have not been present, I have not been taking care of myself,  I have not been a good business partner…just on all accounts felt like I was failing this week. I got caught up in thinking I could handle too much at such a pivotal time in our lives. Next time I move across the country I’m going to jump pack my schedule 🙃
I’m not posting to get sympathy, I’m the one who over commits and let’s myself get so worked up and stressed out over unimportant things. But just posting to show a different side of my life. People often comment that I seem like I do it all, and when I like to think I can I definitely have shit weeks like everyone else 🤍

Yesterday we lost my dad.
Words cannot express the immense love and gratitude I have for this amazing man. He provided me with the most wonderful childhood filled with love, laughter, and cherished memories.
As I navigate this new chapter without him, I hold onto the lessons he taught me and the legacy he leaves behind. Forever grateful for the time we shared and the impact he made on my life. Rest in peace, Dad. You will be deeply missed, but your love will forever live on in my heart 🤍

🤍 10 YEARS 🤍

Over this past decade, we have shared countless unforgettable memories, conquered obstacles together, and grown in ways we never imagined possible. But through it all, I never truly appreciated the depth of your love  until this past week.  You have shown me what it truly means to be there for someone, not just in the good times, but during the darkest moments as well. Your support and compassion have been a constant source of comfort for me and my family, and for that, I am eternally grateful. Happy anniversary @cp0031

🕊️🤍When there were a lot of tears yesterday we also remembered dad with smiles and laughter. It was a great day celebrating the life he lived and the love he shared

Thank you for every single message, for the kind words, for the flowers and gift baskets. Thank to the friends who dropped off food, who drove or flew across the country to be there with us yesterday. It all means so much and so grateful to have such an amazing group of people who care so much for me and my family 🤍

✨ Merry Christmas ✨

It took me 28 years to discover the transformative power of prioritizing my health over fixating on a number on the scale. In a society that bombards us with messages about diets, calorie counting, and the notion that our worth is determined by our weight, I found myself grappling with a distorted perception of food. I saw it as the enemy, rather than an invaluable source of nourishment that could fuel my body and uplift my overall well-being. Like countless women, I became entrapped in the allure of that elusive number on the scale, constantly weighing myself and succumbing to the promises of quick-fix diet plans. I mistakenly believed that consuming pre-packaged “healthy” meals and spending countless hours on the treadmill would lead me to true happiness. 

However, I am now incredibly grateful for breaking free from the chains of this harmful mindset and finally discovering what authentic health truly encompasses. As I navigate through life as a mother to precious little girls, I so badly want to shield them from the same pitfalls I encountered. I am determined to spare them from spending decades consumed by the torment of diet obsession and the relentless pursuit of an arbitrary number on the scale. 

Therefore, I encourage you to exercise utmost mindfulness in the way you speak about food, weight, and dieting in the presence of these young, impressionable ears. Let us focus on fostering a nurturing environment that empowers our future generations to embrace their bodies, prioritize holistic well-being, and cultivate a relationship with food that is rooted in actual health.
